
* Course: paul Mobbs. A practical guide to sustainable IT. APC, 2002.

URL = http://www.apc.org/en/system/files/Section2.pdf [http://greeningit.apc.org full version]

", a hands-on guide to working with everyday technology  in an environmentally conscious way."


=Description=

"examines the way in which our use of information systems 
interacts with the human environment. It encourages you to think 
about the context in which we use computers and the internet, how 
our choices effect the wider environment, and more importantly how 
global economic and environmental issues are inextricably tied to our 
use of information technology. This not only includes the direct impacts of power consumption, or the mining of minerals, but also the 
changes to the economy that have resulted from the greater technological development and mechanisation of what I call the “human system” – the complex and interlinked network of interactions that we 
have created for ourselves."
(http://www.apc.org/en/system/files/Section2.pdf)


